The paper discusses the use of artificial neural networks in machine learning, which is a topic covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which specifically deals with neural networks and their applications. The second most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers a broad range of topics related to machine learning. The third likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which also covers a broad range of topics related to AI and machine learning. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with image and video analysis, a common application of neural networks. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with control systems and optimization, which are relevant to the optimization of neural networks discussed in the abstract.
